<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Zephyr merge list</title>

<style>
/* Theme: every color lives in a variable so light and dark stay in sync. */
:root {
	--bg: #f6f7f9;
	--panel: #ffffff;
	--fg: #1d2531;
	--muted: #5d6b83;
	--border: #dce2eb;
	--accent: #6e37c8;
	--ok: #1a7f37;
	--ok-bg: #def0e3;
	--warn: #7d5c00;
	--warn-bg: #fdeeba;
	--bad: #b42323;
	--bad-bg: #fbe2e2;
	--neutral-bg: #e8ecf2;
	--stripe: #eef1f6;          /* even-row zebra band */
	--row-ready: #e4f6ea;       /* ready rows, overrides the zebra band */
	--row-hover: #e2e8f2;
	--header-bg: #333f67;
	--header-fg: #ffffff;
}
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
	:root {
		/* Lifted off pure black: the page, the panel and the zebra band sit
		 * on distinct, clearly separated steps so nothing reads as
		 * "dark on dark". */
		--bg: #10151d;
		--panel: #1e2735;
		--fg: #e8ecf4;
		--muted: #a3b0c6;
		--border: #38445a;
		--accent: #b48cf5;
		--ok: #56d47b;
		--ok-bg: #1c3a28;
		--warn: #edc84f;
		--warn-bg: #3d3410;
		--bad: #f77f7f;
		--bad-bg: #45201f;
		--neutral-bg: #2b3547;
		--stripe: #262f40;          /* even-row zebra band, a step above panel */
		--row-ready: #204a30;       /* clearly green, not near-black */
		--row-hover: #313d52;
		--header-bg: #2c3759;
		--header-fg: #e9eef9;
	}
}

* { box-sizing: border-box; }

/* Use normal document scrolling. The table is responsive, so it stays
 * within the viewport without a second scrolling region. */
body {
	margin: 0;
	padding: 0 var(--pad) 16px;
	background: var(--bg);
	color: var(--fg);
	font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
	font-size: 14px;
	line-height: 1.4;
}

:root { --pad: 24px; }

.page-header { padding-top: 12px; }

/* Keep the side padding from eating the narrow screens. */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
	:root { --pad: 12px; }
	body { padding-bottom: 12px; }
	.page-header { padding-top: 8px; }
}

a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

/* ---- Page header ------------------------------------------------------ */

.page-header { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.page-header h1 { margin: 4px 0 0; font-size: 21px; }
.page-header .subtitle { color: var(--muted); margin: 0; }

/* The help is a quiet inline link, not a standalone button, so it costs
 * no vertical space of its own. */
.help-link {
	padding: 0;
	background: none;
	border: none;
	color: var(--accent);
	font: inherit;
	font-weight: 600;
	cursor: pointer;
	white-space: nowrap;
}
.help-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

/* ---- Summary bar ------------------------------------------------------- */

/* Keep the update time and CI status together in one compact line. */
.metabar {
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	flex-wrap: wrap;
	gap: 8px 14px;
	margin: 10px 0;
	padding: 8px 14px;
	background: var(--panel);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: 8px;
	font-size: 13px;
}
.metabar .meta-label {
	color: var(--muted);
	font-weight: 600;
	margin-right: 4px;
}
.metabar .meta-sep { color: var(--border); }
#update-timestamp.stale { color: var(--warn); font-weight: 600; }
#update-timestamp.very-stale { color: var(--bad); font-weight: 600; }

.ci-badges { display: inline-flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; vertical-align: middle; }

.ci-badge {
	display: inline-block;
	padding: 1px 8px;
	border-radius: 999px;
	font-size: 12px;
	background: var(--neutral-bg);
	white-space: nowrap;
}
.ci-badge .lucide {
	width: 1em;
	height: 1em;
	margin-right: 4px;
	vertical-align: -0.15em;
}
.ci-pass { background: var(--ok-bg); color: var(--ok); }
.ci-fail { background: var(--bad-bg); color: var(--bad); }
.ci-cancelled { background: var(--warn-bg); color: var(--warn); }
.ci-running { background: var(--neutral-bg); color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
.ci-running .lucide { animation: ci-spin 2s linear infinite; }
@keyframes ci-spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
	.ci-running .lucide { animation: none; }
}

/* ---- MOTD banner ------------------------------------------------------- */

.motd {
	border: 1px solid var(--bad);
	border-left-width: 6px;
	border-radius: 8px;
	background: var(--bad-bg);
	padding: 10px 14px;
	margin: 12px 0;
}

/* ---- Table ------------------------------------------------------------- */

.table-wrap {
	background: var(--panel);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: 8px;
	/* Let the dense table use the full viewport while keeping its content
	 * aligned with the rest of the page through first/last-cell padding. */
	margin: 0 calc(-1 * var(--pad));
}

.prs { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; }

.prs th, .prs td {
	padding: 3px 10px;
	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
	text-align: left;
	vertical-align: top;
}
.prs th:first-child, .prs td:first-child { padding-left: var(--pad); }
.prs th:last-child, .prs td:last-child { padding-right: var(--pad); }

.prs thead th {
	position: sticky;
	top: 0;
	z-index: 1;
	background: var(--header-bg);
	color: var(--header-fg);
	font-size: 12px;
	white-space: nowrap;
	cursor: help;
	padding-top: 6px;
	padding-bottom: 6px;
	/* Draw the header's bottom separator as an inset shadow that travels
	 * with the sticky cell. A collapsed border stays behind at the
	 * original scroll position and lets a row pixel bleed over the edge. */
	border-bottom: none;
	box-shadow: inset 0 -1px 0 var(--border);
}

.prs tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }

/* Row backgrounds, in increasing order of precedence (later rules win at
 * equal specificity):
 *   1. zebra banding on even rows for readability across wide rows;
 *   2. ready rows are tinted green regardless of parity (this, plus the
 *      three green gate icons, is how "ready" reads now the status column
 *      is gone);
 *   3. hover always wins.
 * Which branch a PR targets is left to the Target column, so no extra
 * per-row shading competes with the banding. */
.prs tbody tr:nth-child(even) { background: var(--stripe); }
.prs tbody tr[data-status="ready"] { background: var(--row-ready); }
.prs tbody tr:hover { background: var(--row-hover); }

.prs td.num, .prs td.gate { white-space: nowrap; }
.prs td.gate { text-align: center; }
.prs th.gate-col { text-align: center; }

.gate-icons {
	display: inline-grid;
	grid-template-columns: 18px 18px 52px;
	align-items: center;
	justify-items: center;
	column-gap: 4px;
	vertical-align: middle;
}
.gate-icon {
	display: inline-flex;
	align-items: center;
	justify-content: center;
	gap: 3px;
}
.gate-icon .lucide {
	width: 16px;
	height: 16px;
	flex: none;
}
.gate-review { justify-self: start; }

.gate-pass { color: var(--ok); font-weight: 600; }
.gate-fail { color: var(--bad); font-weight: 600; }
.gate-wait { color: var(--warn); font-weight: 600; white-space: nowrap; }
.gate-unknown { color: var(--muted); }

.muted { color: var(--muted); }

/* ---- Label tags (shown next to PR titles) ------------------------------ */

.tag {
	display: inline-block;
	padding: 0 6px;
	border-radius: 4px;
	font-size: 11px;
	font-weight: 600;
	white-space: nowrap;
	cursor: default;
}
.tag-hotfix { background: #b60205; color: white; }
.tag-trivial { background: #f9d0b1; color: #402000; }
.tag-override { background: #6f42c1; color: white; }
.tag-oldci { background: #fef2c0; color: #574b00; }
.tag-dismissed { background: #ff69b4; color: #3d0d24; }
.tag-dnm { background: #b60205; color: white; }

/* ---- Footer / misc ----------------------------------------------------- */

.toolbar {
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	gap: 16px;
	flex-wrap: wrap;
	margin: 12px 0;
}

.open-ready-button {
	padding: 6px 14px;
	background: var(--ok);
	color: var(--bg);
	border: none;
	border-radius: 6px;
	font-size: 13px;
	font-weight: 600;
	cursor: pointer;
}
.open-ready-button:hover { filter: brightness(1.15); }

/* ---- Help dialog -------------------------------------------------------- */

/* Slightly larger text than the page: the dialog is meant to be read. */
dialog.help {
	margin: auto;
	max-width: 720px;
	width: calc(100vw - 48px);
	padding: 0;
	background: var(--panel);
	color: var(--fg);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: 12px;
	box-shadow: 0 24px 64px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
	font-size: 15px;
	line-height: 1.55;
}
dialog.help::backdrop { background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5); }

/* The padding lives on the body so clicks on the dialog element itself
 * can only come from the backdrop (see setupHelpDialog). */
.help-body { padding: 20px 28px 24px; }

.help-header {
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	justify-content: space-between;
}
.help-header h3 {
	margin: 0;
	font-size: 19px;
}

.help-close {
	padding: 2px 8px;
	background: none;
	color: var(--muted);
	border: none;
	font-size: 16px;
	cursor: pointer;
}
.help-close:hover { color: var(--fg); }

.help h4 {
	margin: 16px 0 4px;
}
.help td, .help th { padding: 2px 10px 2px 0; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
.help a { color: var(--accent); }

.phase { margin: 16px 0 0; font-size: 13px; }
footer { margin-top: 20px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; }
footer img { vertical-align: middle; }

</style>

<script src="https://unpkg.com/lucide@latest"></script>

<script>
"use strict";

/* Message of the day: maintained on the Zephyr wiki, shown when not "empty". */
function loadMotd() {
	const url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wiki/zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr/Merge-List-MOTD.md";
	fetch(url)
		.then((response) => {
			if (!response.ok) {
				throw new Error("HTTP error: " + response.status);
			}
			return response.text();
		})
		.then((text) => {
			if (text.trim() == "empty") {
				return;
			}
			const banner = document.getElementById("motd");
			banner.textContent = text;
			banner.hidden = false;
		})
		.catch((error) => console.log("motd: " + error));
}

/* Show "12 minutes ago" instead of a raw ISO timestamp. */
const rtf = new Intl.RelativeTimeFormat(undefined, { numeric: "auto" });

function renderUpdateTime() {
	const el = document.getElementById("update-timestamp");
	const then = Date.parse(el.getAttribute("datetime"));
	if (isNaN(then)) {
		return;
	}
	const seconds = Math.round((then - Date.now()) / 1000);

	const minutes = Math.abs(seconds) / 60;
	el.classList.toggle("stale", minutes >= 40 && minutes < 60);
	el.classList.toggle("very-stale", minutes >= 60);

	let text;
	if (Math.abs(seconds) < 60) {
		text = rtf.format(seconds, "second");
	} else if (Math.abs(seconds) < 3600) {
		text = rtf.format(Math.round(seconds / 60), "minute");
	} else if (Math.abs(seconds) < 86400) {
		text = rtf.format(Math.round(seconds / 3600), "hour");
	} else {
		text = rtf.format(Math.round(seconds / 86400), "day");
	}
	el.textContent = text;
	el.title = new Date(then).toString();
}

/* Auto-refresh: poll with a HEAD request once a minute and reload only
 * when the page validators say a new version was actually published,
 * so nothing on screen ever moves for nothing. */
function setupAutoRefresh() {
	let current = null;

	function check() {
		fetch(location.href, { method: "HEAD", cache: "no-store" })
			.then((response) => {
				const version = response.headers.get("ETag") ||
					response.headers.get("Last-Modified");
				if (current && version && version != current) {
					location.reload();
				}
				current = version || current;
			})
			.catch((error) => console.log("auto-refresh: " + error));
	}

	check();
	setInterval(check, 60000);
}

/* Open every ready PR in the table that targets main,
 * each in its own tab. Most browsers allow a single popup per click
 * and silently block the rest (window.open returns null), so count
 * the casualties and tell the user how to lift the limit instead of
 * failing mysteriously. */
function openReadyPRs() {
	const rows = [...document.querySelectorAll(
		'#pr-table tbody tr[data-status="ready"][data-base="main"]')];

	if (rows.length == 0) {
		alert("No ready PRs targeting main.");
		return;
	}
	const blocked = rows.filter((row) => {
		const link = row.querySelector("a");
		return link && window.open(link.href, "_blank") == null;
	}).length;

	if (blocked > 0) {
		alert(`The browser blocked ${blocked} of ${rows.length} tabs. ` +
			"Allow pop-ups for this site (look for the blocked pop-up " +
			"icon in the address bar) to open all ready PRs at once.");
	}
}

/* Close the help dialog when the backdrop is clicked; Esc already works
 * natively. Clicks inside the content land on .help-body, not here. */
function setupHelpDialog() {
	const dialog = document.getElementById("help-dialog");
	dialog.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
		if (event.target == dialog) {
			dialog.close();
		}
	});
}

addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
	lucide.createIcons();
	loadMotd();
	renderUpdateTime();
	setInterval(renderUpdateTime, 1000);
	setupAutoRefresh();
	setupHelpDialog();
});
</script>

</head>

<body>

<div class="page-header">
	<h1>Zephyr merge list</h1>
	<p class="subtitle">Open pull requests that are approved, pass CI, and are
	in line to be merged into
	<a href="https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr">zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr</a>.
	<button class="help-link"
		onclick="document.getElementById('help-dialog').showModal()">How this list
		works</button></p>
</div>

<dialog class="help" id="help-dialog" aria-labelledby="help-title">
	<div class="help-body">
	<div class="help-header">
		<h3 id="help-title">How this list works</h3>
		<button class="help-close" aria-label="Close"
			onclick="document.getElementById('help-dialog').close()">&#10005;</button>
	</div>

	<h4>Which PRs show up here?</h4>
	<p>Every open, non-draft pull request that is approved by reviewers and
	passing CI. Code review is done: this page tracks the final wait for a
	release engineer to apply the project's
	<a href="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/project/release_process.html#pull-request-merge-criteria">merge criteria</a>.</p>

	<h4>The three merge gates</h4>
	<p>A PR is merged once all three pass:</p>
	<ol>
		<li><b>Conflict-free</b>: the PR applies cleanly on its target branch,
		no rebase needed.</li>
		<li><b>Assignee approval</b>: the assigned maintainer approved the PR.
		Auto-passes for hotfixes, unassigned PRs, and authors who are their own
		assignee.</li>
		<li><b>Review time</b>: {{REVIEW_WINDOW_BIZ_HOURS}} business hours since
		the PR became ready for review, so everyone gets a chance to comment.
		{{REVIEW_WINDOW_TRIVIAL_HOURS}} hours for <i>trivial</i> PRs, none for
		<i>hotfixes</i>.</li>
	</ol>
	<p>The <b>Ready to merge?</b> column shows the three gates from left to
	right: merge status, assignee approval, and review time. Green icons mean
	passed, red icons mean action is needed, and the clock counts down the
	hours left. A row whose three icons are all green is tinted green and
	ready to merge &mdash; it will be picked up in the next merge round.</p>

	<h4><a href="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/project/dev_env_and_tools.html#labeling-issues-and-pull-requests-in-github">Labels</a></h4>
	<table>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-hotfix">hotfix</span></td>
			<td>Fixes a broken main branch; merged immediately.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-trivial">trivial</span></td>
			<td>Small, low-risk change; the review window is {{REVIEW_WINDOW_TRIVIAL_HOURS}} hours instead of {{REVIEW_WINDOW_BIZ_HOURS}} business hours.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-override">override required</span></td>
			<td>A release engineer must override a failing or stuck required check to merge.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-oldci">ci 42d</span></td>
			<td>The last full CI run is that many days old; CI should be re-run before merging.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-dismissed">review dismissed</span></td>
			<td>A &ldquo;changes requested&rdquo; review was dismissed by someone else; merits a second look.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-dnm">dnm</span></td>
			<td>Do not merge.</td></tr>
	</table>

	<h4>Release phase</h4>
	<p>During <b>integration</b>, features and fixes merge normally. During
	<a href="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/project/release_process.html#feature-freeze-stabilization-phase">feature
	freeze</a>, only bug fixes and release-blocking work are merged, and PRs
	milestoned for the next release wait.</p>
	</div>
</dialog>

<div class="motd" id="motd" role="alert" hidden></div>

<div class="metabar">
	<span><span class="meta-label">Updated</span><time id="update-timestamp" datetime="{{UPDATE_TIMESTAMP}}">{{UPDATE_TIMESTAMP}}</time></span>
	<span class="meta-sep">|</span>
	<span><span class="meta-label">CI on main:</span><span class="ci-badges">{{CI_STATUS}}</span></span>
</div>

<div class="table-wrap">
<table class="prs" id="pr-table">
	<thead>
	<tr>
		<th title="Pull request number">PR</th>
		<th title="Pull request title and labels">Title</th>
		<th title="Who opened the PR">Author</th>
		<th title="Maintainers assigned to shepherd the PR">Assignees</th>
		<th title="Reviewers whose approval currently stands">Approvers</th>
		<th title="Branch the PR will be merged into">Target</th>
		<th title="Release milestone, if set">Milestone</th>
		<th class="gate-col" title="Ready to merge? Left to right: conflict-free, assignee approval, review time">Ready to merge?</th>
	</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
